news.title: Bogus dreams, deadly homes: The Vasai-Virar real estate scam
news.para: A housing scam in Vasai-Virar endangers homebuyers as construction mafias build unauthorized structures with forged documents. The Ramabai Apartment collapse, claiming 17 lives, highlights the deadly consequences. Affordability attracts buyers, but legal loopholes and bureaucratic indifference enable corrupt developers, leading to a surge in illegal constructions and systemic corruption within the VVCMC.

news.title: Bidders approach Mysuru development body to complete auction process for high value sites
news.para: In Mysuru, 118 bidders are proceeding to purchase sites auctioned by the Mysuru Development Authority. Some quoted extremely high prices, like Rupees two crores for a small plot. Developers are surprised, as bigger plots are available elsewhere for similar prices. Officials deny any scam. Concerns are raised about the impact on real estate and affordability for locals.

news.title: To attract companies, Greater Noida may double FAR
news.para: Greater Noida Industrial Development Authority (GNIDA) has proposed increasing the floor area ratio (FAR) for IT, ITES, and Biotech Park plots from 2 to 4, seeking state government approval. This decision follows demands from existing allottees and new investors, aiming to accommodate the region's growth as an investment hub.

news.title: Ludhiana development body razes illegal colony, warns builders against fleecing residents
news.para: Greater Ludhiana Area Development Authority (Glada) has taken strong action against unauthorized colonies, demolishing illegal constructions in Bhadla village. This special drive aims to protect residents from fraudulent developers offering cheap plots without proper approvals. Glada advises the public to verify colony approvals on their website before investing, warning that unauthorized areas will lack essential services.

news.title: CapitaLand to sell Chennai unit leased to Apple supplier
news.para: CapitaLand is divesting a 750,000 sq ft industrial unit in Chennai leased to Pegatron, a key Apple supplier, with potential bids reaching ₹600 crore. Brookfield, Hines, and Hillhouse Capital are among the interested parties. The facility is significant for iPhone manufacturing in India, producing around 750,000 units, including refurbished models.

news.title: Expedite OC nod for 18 floors in south Mumbai highrise, residents urge CM & BMC chief
news.para: Thirty-four flat occupants vacated the top eighteen floors of Willingdon View in Tardeo. This followed a Bombay High Court deadline. Residents, led by Mangal Prabhat Lodha, met Chief Minister Devendra Fadnavis and BMC Commissioner Bhushan Gagrani. They requested a quick Occupation Certificate for the upper floors. The society claims compliance with fire safety norms. They are willing to pay penalties.

news.title: Bhubaneswar: Residents accuse builder of occupying common areas, neglecting safety issues
news.para: Residents of a Rasulgarh real estate project have accused the builder of illegally occupying common areas for commercial use, causing parking issues and safety concerns. They've filed a grievance citing unauthorized construction, an incomplete compound wall, and water stagnation in the basement. Authorities have been urged to investigate these violations of the Odisha Apartment Act.

news.title: Property prices rise in 45 of 50 cities in Q1 FY26: NHB report
news.para: NHB data reveals that property prices in 45 out of 50 cities increased in the first quarter of 2025-26, with the 50-city Housing Price Index rising by 5.7%. Bengaluru saw the highest appreciation at 9.1%, while Howrah experienced the maximum decline at 6.1%. Home loan interest rates also moderated by 100 basis points in February 2025.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh RERA cautions people against unregistered real estate agents
news.para: Andhra Pradesh RERA has warned the public against dealing with unregistered real estate agents, mandating registration within 30 days to comply with the RERA Act of 2016. APRERA Chairperson S Suresh Kumar emphasized that only 248 agents are registered, while thousands operate informally. The authority is expediting decisions on pending project applications and has empowered members to conduct hearings.

news.title: Singapore's CapitaLand C-REIT to raise $294 million in Shanghai listing
news.para: CapitaLand Commercial C-REIT plans to raise 2.1 billion yuan through a Shanghai Stock Exchange listing, issuing 400 million units. This move, approved by Chinese regulators, aligns with CapitaLand Investment's strategy to expand its funds under management using onshore capital. Expected by Q4 2025, it will be China's first internationally sponsored retail REIT.

news.title: Gorakhpur: Record land allotment to GIDA, ₹5,800 crore investments in 2025
news.para: Gorakhpur, once overlooked by investors, is rapidly emerging as an industrial hub, attracting major national and multinational companies. GIDA reports a record allocation of 182 acres for 54 new units, representing ₹5,800 crore in capital investment and 8,500 jobs.

news.title: Mundhwa society residents question inclusion in slum rehabilitation plan in Pune
news.para: Residents of Sarvodaya Cooperative Housing Society in Mundhwa are protesting their society's inclusion as a slum in the 2017 development plan. They claim their land was wrongly classified, and residents falsely listed as slum dwellers. A complaint has been filed with the Slum Rehabilitation Authority (SRA). Residents fear the SRA project will reduce their living space.

news.title: Now, settle violations in pattayam land
news.para: The Kerala cabinet has approved rules to implement the Kerala Land Assignment (Amendment) Act, aiming to regularize violated pattayam land and permit regulated alternative uses. Chief Minister Pinarayi Vijayan stated the move resolves long-standing high-range issues, following broad consultations and unanimous assembly passage.

news.title: Lucknow development body's digital databank to help simplify map approval process
news.para: The Lucknow Development Authority has launched a digital databank to streamline map approvals, eliminating the need for multiple NOCs. This centralised system contains land records from various departments, enabling officials to quickly determine plot ownership. A two-week deadline has been set for external agency approvals; if no response is received, the LDA will proceed independently.

news.title: Bombay HC order 11 members of four dilapidated Vasai buildings to vacate, allow redevelopment
news.para: The Bombay High Court has mandated minority residents of four dilapidated buildings in Vasai West to vacate their flats, emphasizing that obstruction hinders redevelopment. The court acknowledged the majority's decision for redevelopment and cautioned the dissenting members against impeding the process.

news.title: Morbi ceramics industry wants GST reduced to 5%
news.para: The ceramics industry in Morbi, a major tile producer, is requesting a GST reduction. They want the rate lowered from 18% to 5%. The Morbi Ceramic Manufacturers Association argues tiles are a necessity, not a luxury. Lowering GST would help small businesses and boost related sectors. Trade bodies across India support this appeal to the Union finance minister.

news.title: Jet Airways to transfer Mumbai office space lease for ₹370 crore
news.para: Jet Airways, currently in liquidation after ceasing operations in 2019, has agreed to transfer the lease of its Mumbai office space to Parthos Properties Pvt Ltd for Rs 370.25 crore. This transfer, part of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code process following a Supreme Court order in November 2024, is pending approval from the Mumbai Metropolitan Region Development Authority.

news.title: Nagpur: I-T dept finds ‘selective’ under-reporting of realty deals transactions by sub registrars
news.para: An income tax probe in Nagpur has revealed selective underreporting of property transactions by sub-registrars' offices, particularly involving specific builders. Deals worth crores were not reported in the Statement of Financial Transactions, leading to scrutiny of thousands of taxpayers' returns. Property registrar officers have initiated an internal reconciliation of records.

news.title: Gaursons Group to mortgage mall to clear ₹315 crore dues for registry of over 2,000 flats
news.para: GNIDA has conditionally approved Gaursons Group's proposal to mortgage part of Gaur City Mall to secure farmer compensation dues. This move aims to enable the execution of approximately 2,100 pending sub-lease deeds across three housing projects, offering relief to residents awaiting legal ownership. An independent valuation will assess the mall's security value before registries can proceed.

news.title: Evergrande: China's indebted, delisted property behemoth
news.para: Evergrande, a major Chinese property developer, faced delisting from Hong Kong Stock Exchange. The company struggled with debt after new regulations in 2020. This situation reflects a broader downturn in China's property sector. The delisting highlights challenges in China's economy. Experts suggest China needs a new growth engine. The Evergrande collapse serves as a lesson for policymakers.
